cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new method of Blockchain formation for reliable storage of personal data and emphasizes the level of security and access control to this information.
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the structure of the information system and proposes a new structure of smart ID-cards and information on these cards.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper deals with personal data and privacy issues.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new system for storing and accessing personal data.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of Blockchain for distributed storage of personal data.
